<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by lynn on 11-08-2001 07:51 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[b](1)Who started Larian?[/b]
Swen, better known as Lar

[b] (2)When? [/b]
Hmm… we started already making games in the early 90’s, but without having a company. We called ourselves ‘The Larian Empire’, hey, think big !  ;) But Larian Studios was founded in 1996.

[b] (3)What was the first game they developed? [/b]
We already started developing several, but brought one to the market: [URL=http://www.larian.com/Site/english/ledwars/ledwars.html]The L.E.D.Wars[/URL]  which is apparently not forgotten at all: very often I get emails where to buy the game, when we will create some extra levels,…

[b] (4)When came the idea for making an RPG? [/b]
Uh… long time ago already. I think it was 1992.

Alrik was quite right with his information.

But our first RPG was not “Unless, The Treachery of Death”, it was “Ragnarök”. You should see our graphics then  ;) But we were very proud about them ! Actually I can’t remember very well why we changed that name… I think we renamed it Unless, because then we prepared a demo to show to several publishers, and this title was maybe better ?… It’s too long ago, sorry   ;)

Then there was the famous LMK…

And in 1999 we started developing a brand new rpg:  :div: !

[b] (5)From who? [/b]
It was Lar’s idea.

[b] (6)Who is the "BIG BOSS"?[/b]
Lynn, uh no sorry, Lar  :D


------------------
[i]They say don't judge a book by its cover, and in equal measure don't judge a game by its name[/i]</TEXTAREA>
